Text: I would have to become a singularity, \n and seal the darkness within the black hole.
Hey, do you remember? \n You stopped me \n 100 years ago.
The Creator, Bit, told me something, after I \n recovered the memories I lost a century ago.
I never thought I'd see \n you again. I guess we \n have Bit to thank.
I'd do anything \n to protect this \n world.
The destructive force \n that will return the \n world to nothing.
There is only one way \n left to protect the \n light from the dark...
I have to be heavier if I want to resist this wind!
I need to take out all those cores.
But I have to stop that thing!
It just keeps coming back to life!
After all you've \n done for us...
We have to do \n whatever we \n can to help you!
Don't worry, I can \n control it this time!

I'm still Cecie in here, 
 and I'll do whatever 
 it takes to stop that 
 thing!
Please, Kat, now! \n Take down that \n monster!
That core's different from the others, I have to break it!
Even if you steal my power, I won't give up!
Your power to control gravity is gone!
Special attacks and Stasis Fields have been locked!
Little One, why do you endure such pain?
Whether or not you accept it...
Everything will return to nothing, \n the world cannot escape that fate.
You have fought so bravely. \n There is no need to suffer any more.
Accept the world I bring forth, \n and you will have everything you desire.
The people you love. \n You can have it all.
You won't even remember this deal.
A world without end. \n A world forever at peace.
Little One, there is nothing more to worry you.
Accept my world. \n It's your best and only choice.
That's why \n I have to go.
But I'm so much \n stronger now than \n I was then.
